Anonymous Thu 19 May 2022 16:30:38 No.47847398 Report
Quoted By: >>47847543
>>47846947
It depends entirely on how intensely you want the chemistry & romance to unfold. If it's a short slice story, you can make the embers crackle throughout without any actual sexings until much later. If it's an action piece, you have to factor in adrenaline and life-or-death situations bringing two people closer than they'd ever imagined. They can be endeared to one another and even express it physically without being too lewd; I like slowburn with some clear romantic escalation, letting the heat wax to a fever pitch... and then back off, get interrupted, something happens and the inferno flickers before ebbing to a controlled flame again.

So... less as a reward to readers for sticking around, more as a hallmark of your plot that underscores a dramatic turning point in your story, but teased throughout so you, as writer, and we, as readers, have something worth striving with your characters for until that point. The reprieve of a satisfactory conclusion is reward in itself for all involved.
